article_title: Preserved lands include former elk farm along Stony Creek
article_text: Will Sherard, one of Milwaukee’s most notorious landlords, has routinely paid the minimum on fines for hundreds of building code violations, even as he buys new properties. That game may be ending.

article_metadata.title: Photos: Preserved lands include former elk farm along Stony Creek

og.description: Stony Creek flows through a 34-acre former elk farm in the Town of Farmington, which is one of two properties purchased by the Milwaukee Metropolitan Sewerage District and the Ozaukee Washington Land Trust.
